sequenceDiagram
  actor U as User
  participant B as update.go updateBoard
  participant G as model.go gates()
  participant Q as drill.go quickView
  participant VP as viewer

  Note over U,VP: FR-10 — answer a needs-you gate by its number key
  U->>B: press "1".."9"
  B->>B: gateNumberKey(key) → n
  B->>G: gates() (WaitingForInput cards, board order)
  G-->>B: []gate
  alt n within range
    B->>B: jumpToGate(n): focus gate.col/row + reflowColumns
    B->>Q: quickView(gate.feature)
    Q->>VP: open plan.md (plan gate) / report.md (uat gate)
    VP-->>U: read-only view; esc returns to board, gate card focused
    Note over U,B: then the board move key acts — [m] accept / [d] ship / [m] resume
  else n out of range
    B-->>U: status "no gate n — K need you (1..K)"
  end
